Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced). Core and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(cored and thinly sliced). Quarter @lime{1}(quartered).

Pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry; slice crosswise into ½-inch strips and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Generously drizzle @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a very hot pan. Add onion, green pepper, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add steak and @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until steak is cooked to desired doneness, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

In the last minute of cooking, stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} and a small splash of water. Cook, stirring, until water has evaporated, ~{30-60%seconds}. Remove pan from heat and stir in a squeeze of lime (big squeeze for 4).

While steak mixture cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave for ~{30%seconds}.

Serve tortillas, steak mixture, @pico de gallo{4%ounce}, @guacamole{1/2%cup}, @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}, @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon}, and remaining lime wedges family style and let everyone build their own tacos!

> Steaks are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.